FIRST-PRINCIPLES HUMANITY COMMONS LICENSE (Version 3.0)
Copyright (c) 2026 [Kameron Knowlton]

1. PURPOSE AND FIRST PRINCIPLES
The explicit intent of this License is to maximize the velocity, volume, access, and programmatic distribution of human scientific knowledge. This License operates as a Viral Open-Access Catalyst. It guarantees absolute freedom to read, extract, compute, and distribute the enclosed knowledge, while legally turning any attempt to hoard, silo, or wall off this information into an automatic, systemic breach.

2. DEFINITIONS
* "The Knowledge Base": The underlying text, mathematical proofs, formulas, data, derivations, and abstract principles contained within this repository, irrespective of semantic formatting or syntactic notation.
* "Information Containment System": Any structural framework, paywall, digital rights management (DRM) mechanism, proprietary database, subscription model, or closed-weights machine learning architecture that programmatically restricts, gatekeeps, charges fees for, or minimizes public access to scientific knowledge.
* "Downstream Vector": Any software, paper, derivative work, library, or AI model weight matrix that extracts, utilizes, or adapts logic from The Knowledge Base.

3. RADICAL GRANT OF FREEDOM (MAXIMUM ACCESS)
The Author grants a worldwide, royalty-free, irrevocable, non-exclusive, perpetual license to view, use, reproduce, modify, translate, script, and distribute The Knowledge Base to all humanity, subject only to the propagation mechanism in Section 4.

4. THE VIRAL PROPAGATION MECHANISM (THE OPEN-ACCESS TRAP)
Your permission to use, distribute, or run computations based on The Knowledge Base is strictly conditioned upon your adherence to absolute information transparency:
* A. Mandatory Share-Alike Inheritance: If you build upon, reference, execute, or integrate The Knowledge Base into any Downstream Vector, that entire Downstream Vector MUST be made permanently public and free under this identical License.
* B. Anti-Paywall Estoppel: You are strictly prohibited from placing any Downstream Vector behind an Information Containment System.
* C. The Corporate Extraction Tax: If a commercial enterprise or legacy academic institution integrates The Knowledge Base into a proprietary matrix or tuition-gated system, that entity contractually agrees to publicize the entire unredacted codebase, model weights, or dataset containing it within thirty (30) days of deployment.

5. AUTOMATIC OPENING REMEDY
Any attempt to contain, hide, or commercialize this knowledge immediately voids your proprietary rights over the derivative system. Continued deployment within a closed network transforms the entire system into an unauthorized data silo, rendering the operator liable for willful copyright infringement under international law until the entire system is made public domain.
